<emphasis id="B97CC813ED0EFFB3FF70FA24B54F6DBA" box="[212,310,1468,1492]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="2549">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB71401ED0EFFB3FF70FA7CB6ED6E75" blockId="33.[212,1172,1468,1659]" pageId="33" pageNumber="2549">
<taxonomicName id="4C086F82ED0EFFB3FF70FA7CB5866D92" authorityName="Winfield and Ortiz" authorityYear="2013" box="[212,511,1508,1532]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Paracaprella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="33" pageNumber="2549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guerragarciai">
<emphasis id="B97CC813ED0EFFB3FF70FA7CB5866D92" box="[212,511,1508,1532]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="2549">Paracaprella guerragarciai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily distinguished from all species in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C086F82ED0EFFB3FF70F99CB51B6E72" authorityName="Mayer" authorityYear="1890" box="[212,354,1540,1564]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Paracaprella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="33" pageNumber="2549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97CC813ED0EFFB3FF70F99CB51B6E72" box="[212,354,1540,1564]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="2549">Paracaprella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the setose dorsal body.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB71401ED0EFFB3FF5AF9BBB7A26E15" blockId="33.[212,1172,1468,1659]" pageId="33" pageNumber="2549">
This species is the second caprellid species discovered and described originally from the 
<collectingRegion id="49CCDAE3ED0EFFB3FEE4F9DBB50D6E35" box="[320,372,1603,1627]" country="Papua New Guinea" name="Gulf" pageId="33" pageNumber="2549">Gulf</collectingRegion>
of 
<collectingRegion id="49CCDAE3ED0EFFB3FE39F9DBB58C6E35" box="[413,501,1603,1627]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="33" pageNumber="2549">Mexico</collectingRegion>
, since 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9969F0ED0EFFB3FDE6F9DBB6A46E35" author="Mayer P" box="[578,733,1603,1627]" pageId="33" pageNumber="2549" pagination="1 - 160" refId="ref23348" refString="Mayer P. 1903. Die Caprellidae der Siboga-Expedition. Siboga Exped. 34: 1 - 160." type="journal article" year="1903">Mayer (1903)</bibRefCitation>
discovered 
<taxonomicName id="4C086F82ED0EFFB3FCC1F9DCB7AF6E32" authorityName="Steinberg and Dougherty" authorityYear="1957" box="[869,982,1604,1628]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Deutella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="33" pageNumber="2549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incerta">
<emphasis id="B97CC813ED0EFFB3FCC1F9DCB7AF6E32" box="[869,982,1604,1628]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="2549">D. incerta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(described as 
<taxonomicName id="4C086F82ED0EFFB3FBDFF9DCB5596E15" authorityName="Steinberg and Dougherty" authorityYear="1957" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Deutella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="33" pageNumber="2549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incerta">
<emphasis id="B97CC813ED0EFFB3FBDFF9DCB5596E15" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="2549">L. incerta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in the 
<collectingRegion id="49CCDAE3ED0EFFB3FEDFF9FBB58E6E15" box="[379,503,1635,1659]" country="United States of America" name="Mississippi" pageId="33" pageNumber="2549">Mississippi</collectingRegion>
– 
<collectingRegion id="49CCDAE3ED0EFFB3FDA0F9FBB6156E15" box="[516,620,1635,1659]" country="United States of America" name="Alabama" pageId="33" pageNumber="2549">Alabama</collectingRegion>
continental shelf a century ago.
</paragraph>
